The paper deals with the problem of discovering order dependencies in databases, which is a topic in the field of database management systems (DBMS). Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm that uses machine learning techniques to discover order dependencies, which could place it in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves pruning rules and search space optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
